data.enText: idea/opinion
an idea, a feeling or an opinion that you get about sb/sth, or that sb/sth gives you
a general/an overall impression

data.chText: 对某人 / 某事物的印象好 / 不好
data.enText: to get a good/bad impression of sb/sth
an initial/a lasting impression

data.chText: 他给我的第一印象不错。
data.enText: My first impression of him was favourable.

data.chText: 我并不觉得他们不满于当时的状况。
data.enText: I did not get the impression that they were unhappy about the situation.

data.chText: 依我看问题还是蛮多的。
data.enText: My impression is that there are still a lot of problems.

data.chText: 她给人的印象是特别忙。
data.enText: She gives the impression of being very busy.

data.chText: 尽量微笑，不要让人误以为你很冷漠。
data.enText: Try and smile. You don't want to give people the wrong impression (= that you are not friendly) .
effect
the effect that an experience or a person has on sb/sth
a big impression

data.chText: 他的印度之行对他的触动很大。
data.enText: His trip to India made a strong impression on him.

data.chText: 你如果真的想给人留下好印象，就得表演得更好。
data.enText: You'll have to play better than that if you really want to make an impression (= to make people admire you) .

data.chText: 我的话丝毫没有对她起作用。
data.enText: My words made no impression on her.
drawing
a drawing showing what a person looks like or what a place or a building will look like in the future

data.chText: 这是一位艺术家对未来新运动场作的印象画。
data.enText: This is an artist's impression of the new stadium.
amusing copy of sb

data.chText: （对某人举止言谈的）滑稽模仿
data.enText: an amusing copy of the way a person acts or speaks

data.chText: 他滑稽地模仿了汤姆∙汉克斯。
data.enText: He did his impression of Tom Hanks.
false appearance
an appearance that may be false

data.chText: 巧妙的照明会让人有屋子空间增大的感觉。
data.enText: Clever lighting creates an impression of space in a room.
mark
a mark that is left when an object is pressed hard into a surface
book
all the copies of a book that are printed at one time, with few or no changes to the contents since the last time the book was printed
(be) under the impression that…
believing, usually wrongly, that sth is true or is happening

data.chText: 我还以为已经完工了呢。
data.enText: I was under the impression that the work had already been completed.

simple_means.memory_skill: impress 盖印；留印象 + ion 表名词 → 印象；感想

ex.chText: 一棵倒下的树在坚硬的泥地上留下了清晰的压痕。
ex.enText: A fallen tree has left a clear impression in the hardening mud.

synonyms.bx: 指按压某一柔软表面所留下的痕迹。

ex.enText: There is a dent in my car.

ex.chText: 你看见门上那一大块凹坑了吗？
ex.enText: Did you see that large dent in the door?

synonyms.bx: 指因碰撞而在某物表面造成的凹陷痕迹。

ex.chText: 那个苹果上有咬过的痕迹。
ex.enText: There is a bite mark on the apple.

ex.chText: 她想知道为什么他的身上有几道抓痕。
ex.enText: She wanted to know why there were several scratch marks on his body.

synonyms.bx: 指割痕、孔洞或其他细小的损坏痕迹。

ex.zh: 深刻的印象；强烈的感觉

data.enText: (be) under the impression that…
believing, usually wrongly, that sth is true or is happening

data.chText: 我还以为已经完工了呢。
data.enText: I was under the impression that the work had already been completed.

tr: the act of pressing one thing on or into the surface of another
example: he watched the impression of the seal on the hot wax

tr: an impressionistic portrayal of a person
example: he did a funny impression of a politician

tr: (dentistry) an imprint of the teeth and gums in wax or plaster
example: the dentist took an impression for use in preparing an inlay
I wanted to create an impression of success
she retained that bold effect in her reproductions of the original painting

tr: a vague idea in which some confidence is placed
example: his impression of her was favorable
what are your feelings about the crisis?
it strengthened my belief in his sincerity
I had a feeling that she was lying

tr: a clear and telling mental image
example: he described his mental picture of his assailant
he had no clear picture of himself or his world
the events left a permanent impression in his mind

tr: all the copies of a work printed at one time
example: they ran off an initial printing of 2000 copies

tr: a symbol that is the result of printing or engraving
example: he put his stamp on the envelope

tr: a concavity in a surface produced by pressing
example: he left the impression of his fingers in the soft mud

value.def: Your impression of a person or thing is what you think they are like, usually after having seen or heard them. Your impression of a situation is what you think is going on.

example.ex: What were your first impressions of college?...
example.tran: 你对大学的第一印象是什么？

example.ex: My impression is that they are totally out of control...
example.tran: 我的感觉是它们完全失去了控制。

example.ex: There was a general impression that tomorrow meant a fresh start.
example.tran: 普遍的感觉是明天意味着一个新的开始。

gramarinfo.label: oft poss N, N <l>of</l> n, N that

value.def: If someone gives you a particular impression, they cause you to believe that something is the case, often when it is not.

example.ex: I don't want to give the impression that I'm running away from the charges...
example.tran: 我不想给人一种我在逃避指控的感觉。

example.ex: He cleverly inserted mirrors above the window to create an impression of space.
example.tran: 他巧妙地在窗子上面镶嵌了几面镜子，以营造一种空间感。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N that, N <l>of</l> n

value.def: An impression is an amusing imitation of someone's behaviour or way of talking, usually someone well-known.

example.ex: He did impressions of Sean Connery and James Mason.
example.tran: 他对肖恩·康纳利和詹姆斯·梅森进行了滑稽模仿。

value.def: An impression of an object is a mark or outline that it has left after being pressed hard onto a surface.

example.ex: ...the world's oldest fossil impressions of plant life.
example.tran: 世界上最古老的植物化石印痕

value.def: If someone or something makes an impression, they have a strong effect on people or a situation.

example.ex: He has told me his plans and he's made a good impression on me...
example.tran: 他告诉了我他的计划,给我留下了一个好印象。

example.ex: The aid coming in has made no impression on the horrific death rates.
example.tran: 逐渐到达的救援对可怕的死亡率并没有起到什么作用。

value.def: If you are under the impression that something is the case, you believe that it is the case, usually when it is not actually the case.

example.ex: He had apparently been under the impression that a military coup was in progress.
example.tran: 他显然以为一场军事政变正在酝酿中。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to press, to force 挤压；逼迫
rootsaffixes.title: press

partsOfSpeech.dec: com 加强 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 压缩
com 加强 + press 挤压；逼迫 + ible 可…的 → 可压缩的
com 加强 + press 挤压；逼迫 + ion 表动作 → 压缩
de 向下 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 向下压 → 使情绪低下
depress 压下；使沮丧 + ion 表名词 → 沮丧；萧条
ex 出 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 把〔思想〕挤出来 → 表达
express 表达 + ion 表名词 → 表达；表情
im 进入 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 压进去 → 留印象
impress 盖印；留印象 + ion 表名词 → 印象；感想
impress 盖印；留印象 + ive …的 → 给人深刻印象的
op 加强 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 拼命压 → 压迫，虐待
oppress 压迫，虐待 + ion 表名词 → 压迫；苦难
press 挤压；逼迫 + ing 正…的 → 急迫的
press 挤压；逼迫 + ure 表结果 → 压力
re 回 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 压回去 → 镇压；抑制〔感情〕
sup 下 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 压下去 → 镇压；忍住
suppress 镇压；忍住（眼泪等）+ ion 表名词 → 镇压
